<p>
    2.13. All Participants agree to abide by the following procedures:
</p>
<p>
    a) Refusal to co-operate with the Inspector is a ground for disqualification.
</p>
<p>
    b) Participants shall deliver, immediately upon request, to an Inspector any hypodermic syringe, needle or any other device, swabs, cloths or other
    material, or samples, or any medicine, preparation or substance (whether in liquid or other form), in the possession or control of the Participant, his or
    her fitter, agents, or persons acting on his or her behalf, for the purpose or inspection or laboratory analysis.
</p>
<p>
    c) All entries and property of the Participants are subject to inspection by the Inspectors. Participants shall co-operate with the Inspectors and shall:
</p>
<p>
    · provide access to the animal(s) owned or exhibited by the Participant at the Show;
</p>
<p>
    · provide all information reasonably required by the Inspector(s) in connection with such inspections;
</p>
<p>
    · provide samples of urine, milk, blood, or any other body fluids suitable for analysis from the relevant animal(s), if so requested;
</p>
<p>
    · allow all udders of any bovine animal(s) owned or exhibited by the Participant at the Show to be scanned on request of an Inspector.
</p>
<p>
    · remain at the head of the animal and not touch the udder until scanning has taken place.
</p>
<p>
    d) Participants shall remove any udder supports, blankets or other objects limiting the ability of the inspector to undertake a thorough inspection of any
    bovine animal(s) owned or exhibited by the Participant at the Show.
</p>
<p>
    e) Participants agree to act at all times in accordance with the Rules and Regulations and the Procedures, and will accept any final decision made
    thereunder.
</p>
<p>
    f) Participants may be liable for all veterinary expenses in relation to their animal(s), if required by the Organiser, while their animal(s) is/are at the
    Venue.
</p>
<p>
    g) Bovine Animals whether individually restricted or part of a herd restricted under the Tuberculosis (England) Order 2007 (as amended) shall not be
    permitted to attend the Show.
</p>
<p>
    h) Participants shall ensure that Bovine Animals from high TB risk areas (meaning areas in England and Wales where cattle must be tested for tuberculosis
    annually) have received a clear TB test prior to such animals being transported to the Venue as required under the Tuberculosis (England) (Amendment) Order
    2012. Testing must have taken place not more than 60 days prior to the date of transportation to the Venue (from date of injection).
</p>
<p>
    i) Details of the test results be must sent to the Show Organiser prior to the Show or be presented to the Chief Vet or Inspector immediately upon the
    arrival of each relevant Bovine Animal at the Venue. The Show Organiser has the right to refuse cattle entry to the Show if the test results are not
    presented.
