    3. Standard Procedures and Penalties for Enforcing the Rules and Regulations
</p>
<p align="left">
    The purpose of these procedures is to put into effect the Rules and Regulations as published by the Organiser from time to time. Where there is any
    conflict between the Rules and Regulations and these Procedures, the Rules and Regulations shall prevail to the extent of the conflict.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.1. All Participants must sign the applicable agreement(s) annexed to these Rules and Regulations to abide by the Rules and Regulations, either as a
    separate document or as part of the entry form. All Participants agree that they have read and accepted the Rules and Regulations and the Procedures as a
    condition of their participation at the Show.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.2. The Rules Committee for the Show will be responsible for overseeing compliance with the Rules and Regulations.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3. The Inspectors shall monitor compliance of the Rules and Regulations. To help in this regard the Inspectors and the agents or representatives acting
    under the instructions of any Inspector shall have the authority (which each relevant Participant hereby grants) to perform on any Bovine or Ovine Animal
    in the Show at the Venue any of the following:
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3.1. a full body inspection of the animal (including, but not limited to the udder);
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3.2. an ultrasound examination of the udder at any time;
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3.3. a milk out of any individual cow or cows;
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3.4. the collection and testing at any time of any animal's body fluids;
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.3.5. the use at any time of any other technology and other inspections and/or analysis (including autopsy), that an Inspector (or his or her agent or
    representative), acting reasonably, considers may be useful for assessing compliance with the Rules and Regulations.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.4. All Participants at the Show shall provide promptly to the Rules Committee, upon request, such information and shall produce such documents as may be
    required by the Rules Committee for the proper monitoring of compliance with the Rules and Regulations and shall fully co-operate with any inspections.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.5. At any time the Rules Committee reserves the right to ask a Participant to consider withdrawing their Bovine or Ovine Animal from a show class before
    entering the show ring if;
</p>
<p>
    e. a complaint has been received of a possible violation of the Rules and Regulations for Showing Bovine and Ovine Animals concerning the Bovine or Ovine
    Animal to be shown, or
</p>
<p>
    f. the Rules Committee has a reasonable belief that there would be violation of the Rules and Regulations for Showing Bovine and Ovine Animals if the
    Participant's Bovine or Ovine Animal is shown.
</p>
<p>
    If the Participant decides not to show the animal after receiving such a warning, no violation of the Rules and Regulations for Showing Bovine and Ovine
    Animals will be considered to have occurred and no disciplinary measures will be taken against the Participant.
</p>
<p align="left">
    Notwithstanding the above, at any time during the Show, the Rules Committee reserves the right to disqualify a Participant, the Participant's Bovine or
    Ovine Animal(s) or both at the Show, if they believe there has been a violation of the Rules and Regulations, these Procedures, or the Terms and Conditions
    of the Show.
    <s>
    </s>
    <s>
    </s>
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.6. Where, the Rules Committee considers that there has been a violation of the Rules and Regulations, these Procedures, or, as per the Livestock Event
    Terms &amp; Conditions, the Terms and Conditions of the Show, the accused Participant shall be notified of the alleged violation and shall, confidentially,
    be provided with information supporting the basis for the allegation.
</p>
<p align="left">
    3.7. The Rules Committee shall discuss any alleged violation of the Rules and Regulations or other procedures or terms and conditions relating to any
