</h1>
<p>
    Exhibitors making entries in any class are subject to and must observe and conform to these Regulations in addition to the RABDF Rules and Regulations for
    Showing.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>DEFINITIONS</strong>
</p>
<p>
    In these Regulations, unless the context otherwise requires, the under-mentioned expressions shall have the following meaning respectively:
</p>
<p>
    'Exhibitor' means (a) a person or his executor/s or a firm exhibiting livestock: (b) a person or firm who occupies space for the purpose of advertising or
    sale: (c) a person or firm who competes in any competition: and (d) the representative or agent of any of the above.
</p>
<p>
    For the purpose of the Livestock Event, the definition of exhibitor bred is: An animal is defined as Exhibitor Bred if it is born in the U.K. and carries
    the owner's prefix. This includes animals born as a result of embryo transplant.
</p>
<p>
    An animal in joint ownership qualifies as exhibitor bred providing it has been jointly entered and one of the joint owners is the breeder.
</p>
<p>
    'The Organiser' means the Royal Association of British Dairy Farmers.
</p>
<p>
    'The NEC' means National Exhibition Centre, Birmingham B40 1NT.
</p>
<p>
    1. Stall booking forms must be signed and accompanied by the necessary fees and must be received by the 30<sup>th</sup> May 2014. Cheques should be made
    payable to <u>'RABDF'</u> and crossed.
</p>
<p>
    2. Every exhibitor will be held responsible for the correctness of details given on the Entry Form, Animal Admission Card/s, other documents and individual
    exhibitors shall, if called upon to do so, prove their correctness in such manner as the Organiser may require. The Organiser or its officials, in their
    absolute discretion and without assigning any reason therefore, may refuse an entry, or cancel an entry already accepted. Whenever under this Rule an entry
    is refused or cancelled, the fees paid for such an entry, at the discretion of the Organiser, shall be refunded and if refunded, shall be accepted by the
    exhibitor or intending exhibitor in full satisfaction of all claims against the Organiser.
</p>
<p>
    3. Exhibitors or their Stock attendants must take total responsibility for their stock at all times, whilst at the NEC. All persons in charge of exhibits
    will be subject to the orders of the stewards and will be required to parade or exhibit the animals in their charge at such times as may be directed by the
    Stewards. No Stock attendants shall be allowed to lead more than one animal at a time in the Judging rings.
</p>
<p>
    4. Judges: A Judge shall not exhibit in the class, classes or breed in which he or she is officiating.
</p>
<p>
